The '''[[Dean (Christianity)|dean]]s in the [[Church of England]]''' are the senior [[Anglicanism|Anglican]] [[clergy]] who head the [[Chapter (religion)|chapter]] of a [[collegiate church]] (almost all of which are [[cathedral]]s). If they are dean of the [[Diocese|diocesan]] chapter, they are the senior priest of the diocese and often also undertake some other diocesan and civic duties in the area.

